      <data key="edge_doi">10.1105/tpc.107.054148</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">S/G ratio of FAS13 and FS40 lignin was significantly lower than that of wild type; relatively more reduced in syringyl than in guaiacyl units</data>
    </edge>
