      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">4CL1 activity level drives preferential S-unit deposition in poplar: CRISPR-KO gives 34% S reduction vs 5% G reduction (pyMBMS); antisense lines show S/G decline from 1.8-2.3 to 1.1-1.4</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1104/pp.19.01550</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">pyMBMS analysis detected a 30% decrease in S/G ratio; 34% reduction of S-units and a small (5%) reduction of G-units</data>
    </edge>
